== Short Bio 
I am a final year undergrdauate in Electrical Engineering at the Indian Institute of Technology Patna (IITP), India. I am broadly interested in research in Theoretical Computer Science and Communication Theory.
I have been extremely fortunate to be advised by [https://research-information.bris.ac.uk/en/persons/sidharth-sid-jaggi Prof. Sidharth Jaggi] (University of Bristol), [http://www.facweb.iitkgp.ac.in/~amitalok/ Prof. Amitalok J. Budkuley] (IIT Kharagpur), [https://perso-etis.ensea.fr/luzzi/ Prof. Laura Luzzi] (ENSEA, CNRS), and [https://www.iitp.ac.in/index.php/en-us/people-2/faculty/2-uncategorised/194-view-profile-8 Prof. Preetam Kumar] (IIT Patna) in my undergraduate research. \n

I also love playing outdoor sports specially Cricket and Volleyball in my free time.

== Education 
- B.Tech in Electrical Engineering, [https://www.iitp.ac.in/ Indian Institute of Technology Patna] (IIT Patna), Bihar, India. (July. 2018 - Present)
- Class XII (AISSCE), [https://www.gnms.co.in/ Guru Nanak Modern School], Kanpur, U.P, India.
- Class X (AISCE), [https://www.gnms.co.in/ Guru Nanak Modern School], Kanpur, U.P, India. 
== Research Interests 
My specific Research Interests include:
 - Information Theory 
 - Coding Theory
 - Cryptography
 - Information-theoretic Security & Privacy\n

I have also been exploring various related sub-areas, but not limited to Information Theory for Machine Learning, Network Information Theory and Bioinformatics.

== News 
- \[26-08-2021\] Presented a poster on "Rate Positivity for Arbitrarily Varying Channels" at [https://cscit.ie.cuhk.edu.hk/ CSCIT 2021], CUHK, Hong Kong. 
- \[30-07-2021\] Presented our accepted paper on "Commitment over Compound Binary Symmetric Channels" at [https://www.iitk.ac.in/ncc2021/ NCC 2021] conference, Kanpur, India. 
- \[22-07-2021\] Presented a poster with Manideep on "Role of Costs in Commitment over Noisy Channels" at [https://conferences.ece.ubc.ca/nasit2021/ NASIT 2021], UBC, Canada. 
- \[15-06-2021\] Received 2021 [https://www.itsoc.org/news/isit-scholarships-undergraduates-groups-currently-underrepresented-itsoc-0 IEEE ITSoc Undergraduate Scholarship] by *IEEE Information Theory Society*.

